info.title: TM4Web
info.description:
The TM4Web REST API service provides access to TruckMate data dealing with orders, trips and web users. The TM4Web REST API service is not used by the TM4Web program directly but is intended as a supplementary method to access and interact with the TruckMate data. The TruckMate TM4Web REST API license #61140 is required in order to use this API. This license is included with TM4Web but you must request to have it added to your license key. (Contact TruckMate support.)

barcode.description: System-generated scannable barcode for the handling unit.

altBarcode1.description: An alternate scannable barcode for the handling unit.

altBarcode2.description: A second alternate scannable barcode for the handling unit.

cube.description: Cubic dimensional value of the handling unit.

cubeUnits.description: Unit of measure for the cube attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

heightUnits.description: Unit of measure for the height attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

lengthUnits.description: Unit of measure for the length attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

location.description: Identifier for the last known location of the handling unit.

locationTerminalId.description: Numeric ID for the terminal where the handling unit is currently or was last located.

locationTerminalZone.description: Zone code for the terminal where the handling unit is currently or was last located.

locationTimestamp.description: Timestamp for the last known location information.

locationType.description: Type of location referred to by the location attribute.

pallets.description: Pallets that make up the handling unit.

palletUnits.description: Unit of measure for the pallets attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

pieces.description: Pieces that make up the handling unit.

pieceUnits.description: Unit of measure for the pieces attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

temperatureUnits.description: Unit of measure for the temperature attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

status.description: Current location status of this specific handling unit.

statusComment.description: Additional human-readable comments clarifying the last known status of the freight.

volumeUnits.description: Unit of measure for the volume attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

weightUnits.description: Unit of measure for the weight attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

widthUnits.description: Unit of measure for the width attribute. Note that unit types are configurable and may vary per TruckMate instance.

webuserJwtAuth.description: A fresh JSON Web Token expires in four hours. It can be renewed by making a GET request to /login endpoint, or generated by making a POST request to /login endpoint.
